"title": "2321: Jesus Christ, as redeemer",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "2321: jesus christ, as redeemer",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ redeems believers from all forms of sinful bondage and oppression through his death and resurrection. The price of that redemption, his own death, represents a ransom paid to secure the freedom of those held in bondage to sin.</p>\n<h2>The incarnate God as redeemer</h2>\n<h3>God as redeemer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa63:16\">ISA 63:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job19:25\">JOB 19:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:26\">ISA 49:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa59:20\">ISA 59:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:68-Luke1:75\">LUK 1:68–1:75</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ as redeemer</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor1:30\">1CO 1:30</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Forms of bondage from which Jesus Christ redeems believers</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ redeems from slavery to sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:5\">REV 1:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps130:8\">PSA 130:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom3:23-Rom3:24\">ROM 3:23–3:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:18\">ROM 6:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom6:22\">ROM 6:22</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:14\">TIT 2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus3:3-Titus3:5\">TIT 3:3–3:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet3:18\">1PE 3:18</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ redeems from the curse of the law</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:13\">GAL 3:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4-Gal4:5\">GAL 4:4–4:5</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ redeems from empty religion</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:18\">1PE 1:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:3\">GAL 4:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:20\">COL 2:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:14\">HEB 9:14</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ redeems from the power of Satan</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:13\">COL 1:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:18\">ACT 26:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal1:4\">GAL 1:4</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ redeems from the coming judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess1:10\">1TH 1:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom5:9\">ROM 5:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:1-Rom8:2\">ROM 8:1–8:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess5:9\">1TH 5:9</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ redeems from death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:14-Heb2:15\">HEB 2:14–2:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos13:14\">HOS 13:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor15:54-1Cor15:57\">1CO 15:54–15:57</a></p>\n<h2>The means by which Jesus Christ has redeemed believers</h2>\n<h3>Redemption comes through the incarnation of Jesus Christ</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:4-Gal4:5\">GAL 4:4–4:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:3\">ROM 8:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:14\">HEB 2:14</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ redeems by his sacrificial death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:12\">HEB 9:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor5:21\">2CO 5:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:7\">EPH 1:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet1:18-1Pet1:19\">1PE 1:18–1:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev1:5\">REV 1:5</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ redeems by paying a ransom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt20:28\">MAT 20:28</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:45\">MRK 10:45</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:28\">ACT 20:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:15\">HEB 9:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev5:9\">REV 5:9</a></p>\n<h2>The purposes for which Jesus Christ redeems believers</h2>\n<h3>Jesus Christ redeems believers so that their sins may be forgiven</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:7\">EPH 1:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts26:18\">ACT 26:18</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:14\">COL 1:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:15\">HEB 9:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1John1:7\">1JN 1:7</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ redeems believers to make them pure</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Titus2:14\">TIT 2:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor6:19-1Cor6:20\">1CO 6:19–6:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:23\">1CO 7:23</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ redeems believers so that they may receive God's promised blessings</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal3:14\">GAL 3:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:5\">GAL 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:1\">GAL 5:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb9:15\">HEB 9:15</a></p>\n<h3>Jesus Christ redeems believers so that they may receive final redemption</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:23\">ROM 8:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke21:28\">LUK 21:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:14\">EPH 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:30\">EPH 4:30</a></p>",
